The pair of Johns in the name refers to the collaboration of Rogue Brewmaster John Maier and Rogue Master Distiller John Couchot, who distills Rogue Spruce Gin and then supplies the barrels in which this juniper pale ale is aged. A bit of a homegrown beer, "John John Ale" features Rogue Micro Hopyard Revolution hops and the Dare and Risk strains of barley from Rogue's micro farms.
